               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481127-name-638" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-638" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-638" type="surname" value="DAVIS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-638" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS DAVIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a gardener, of Princes-street, Portman-square. On 8th Nov. I laid my scarf on the counter, and went into the parlour, at the back of the shop—in about an hour and a half I heard a cry, went into the shop, and missed it—I have not seen it since.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481127-name-639" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-639" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-639" type="surname" value="PIPER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18481127-name-639" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH PIPER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a servant. I saw Mr. Davis's scarf on the counter, about seven o'clock in the evening—I was in the parlour, and saw the pri<lb></lb>soner come into the shop—I did not know him before—he went on his hands and knees, took the scarf, and ran away—I went out, but did not see him—I described him to the police, and picked him out of seven or eight others on the Friday afterwards.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18481127-name-640" type="witnessName">
